{
  "text": "The findings will provide important information for the use of appropriate pepper cultivars as food ingredients. The phytochemical compound concentrations in the pepper fruit illustrate the importance in choosing a suitable cultivar, which, as a rich source of functional compounds, prevents the development of chronic diseases such as diabetes and cancer [CITATION_1] . Therefore, the aim of the present study is to determine the concentration of functional materials and antioxidant activity as affected by B concentration in the nutrient solution in four C. annuum L. varieties of high use, with the objective to compare their bioactive profiles and use as ingredients in the human diet.",
